{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17500955","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17500955"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:20:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:20:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1700"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1700","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1700"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.18,0.46,0.01,0.03,0.31]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1700"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80240"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1700","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1700"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1700"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65534"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"552"},{"type":"tags","id":"934"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9188"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8383"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8565"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27420"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80240","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80240"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with a four-day history of vague abdominal discomfort and nausea. Her medical history is not immediately available. A plain abdominal X-ray is ordered as part of the assessment. (Image)\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most relevant finding on the X-ray?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["PEG tube","Gastric band","Residual contrast","Calcified gallstones","Swallowed foreign body"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe radiological artifact seen on the abdominal X-ray is a \u003Cstrong\u003Egastric band\u003C/strong\u003E. The gastric band will be visible around the upper part of the stomach, typically just below the oesophagus. It is a ring-shaped silicon band with an attached adjustment port where the band can be adjustment used to help treat obesity. Gastric bands are associated with a high failure rate and have now been superseded by sleeve gastrectomy and roux-en-Y gastric bypass. In this case, the band appears to have slipped and may be responsible for the patient\u0027s current symptoms. It will need to be removed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003EPEG tube\u003C/strong\u003E (percutaneous endoscopic gastrostomy) appears as a radiopaque tube traversing the anterior abdominal wall into the stomach. It typically has a characteristic appearance with a flange or bumper visible within the stomach lumen.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EResidual contrast\u003C/strong\u003E can be seen in abdominal X-rays for patients that have recently had radiopaque contrast material for procedures such as a barium enema or barium swallow. These are typically irregular in shape and take the shape of the stomach or intestinal structure that surrounds it.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERadiopaque, calcified gallstones\u003C/strong\u003E can be present in up to 20% of gallstones. They are typically round and present in the right hypochondriac region where the gallbladder and biliary system reside.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Eswallowed foreign body\u003C/strong\u003E can take any form based on the item that is swallowed! However, it would generally stay confined within the walls of the stomach and intestines.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A gastric band is a radiopaque silicon band that can be found in the epigastric region on abdominal X-rays."],"references":["Abdominal X-ray calcification and artifacts: https://www.radiologymasterclass.co.uk/tutorials/abdo/abdomen_x-ray/anatomy_system_calcium"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65534"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1700"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19533"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19533","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19533"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/1be868c5-1372-4f42-b31d-513a18876c20.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/1be868c5-1372-4f42-b31d-513a18876c20.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":720,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65534","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65534"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-18T17:34:41+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-18T17:35:11+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1700"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80240"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"headi